time complexity: O(n + k log k) where k = 128
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Count frequencies in one pass, sort the 128 possible ASCII characters by frequency, then build the result by repeating each character according to its frequency. Uses constant-size arrays and a single sort, making it very fast and memory-efficient.

